<TABLE width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">

<TR><TD bgcolor="bfbf80"><FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" SIZE="+1" color="4a0000"><B>Silvermesh Leggings</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR><TD bgcolor="cdcd9c">
<FONT FACE="Arial, Verdana, Helvetica" size="-1">

<B>Zone(s)</B>: Greater Faydark &nbsp; &nbsp; <B>Class(es)</B>: Rogue<BR>

<BR>

<B>Quest Details</B>:<BR>
After completing the scouts blade quest, something is mentioned about acquiring your <a href="/equipment/armor_display.cfm?id=236">Silver Mesh Leggings</a>. These are incredible mid-level legs, only superior to ravenscale, and I have NEVER seen an actual pair besides mine, as the quest has a lot of mysterious parts to it. If you are lvl 20+, and have completed the Scouts Blade quest I seriously recommend trying this one out.<BR><BR>

First step, ask the Rogue guildmaster in Kelethin about the Silver Mesh Leggings. He will tell you to retrieve the Gem of Tunare from Faldor Hendrys. While Faldors whereabouts remain unknown, his brother, Elmion Hendrys is supposedly adventuring near The Estate. The estate is Unrest, Elmion is an NPC in the Dagnors Cauldron zone at the camp along with 3 other NPC's. When asked where Faldor is, Elmion laughs and mentions his brother is in Qeynos. Now comes the journey.<BR><BR>

It has been discovered that the only way to force Faldor to spawn is by asking Elmion of his whereabouts, he will spawn anywhere from 10 minutes to 2 hours later (I'll check on those times). At this point, you have one of two options. Run like hell to Qeynos, or get a friend to wait in Dagnor's to trigger the spawn. Beware, the Gem of Tunare Faldor carries is for another quest too, and may be camped at the same time.<BR><BR>

When you reach Qeynos, you have to wait. Faldor spawns in the Rogue guild underneath Crow's tavern. No point in going down there, however, since you cannot fight him down there and he wanders. So best place to wait is in the tavern. Faldor will walk out of the guild sooner or later, do not attack him. Follow him until he walks outside the Qeynos gates and around the corner. When you get far enough from the guards, unleash on him. He hits very hard for his level, don't try to solo him unless you are at least level 
24. Bring some friends for good measure. Once Faldor has been slain, loot the Gem of Tunare which is NO DROP so make sure you loot it.<BR><BR>

Head back to Kelethin, and return the Gem to the guildmaster. You're reward, some very nice experience and the famed <a href="/equipment/armor_display.cfm?id=236">SilverMesh Leggings</a>! Be proud of yourself and show them off to any rogue you see, instant jealousy.
<BR><BR>
NOTE: If the spawn times on Faldor are different please inform me, I camped him without triggering the spawn and it took 5 hours.

</BLOCKQUOTE>


</font>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
